Ask HN: Librarians, how do you find books to buy
text: I've always wondered, how do you know which books to buy for a library? I've heard some libraries track which books are read (but not checked out) and I'm sure libraries know which books are checked out. Is it as simple as looking at these two lists to know what is popular? Do you care about the content of the books or just the general category? Do you look for best sellers?
